<!--
  Channel list for the iptv-org/epg grabber (https://github.com/iptv-org/epg).

  NOTE: this fetch runs in GitHub Actions via .github/workflows/epg.yml, not
  in the Claude sandbox (which has no outbound network).

  HOW IT WORKS.
  Each channel needs:
    site      = a folder name under the grabber's `sites/` directory
    site_id   = that source's own id for the channel
    xmltv_id  = MUST match the `epgId` in data/channels.js so the converter
                (scripts/xmltv-to-guide.mjs) attaches the listings to the card.

  ONLY VERIFIED CHANNELS ARE LISTED HERE.
  Every site_id below was taken from the grabber's own committed channel
  catalogs, so the IDs are real:
    sites/freeview.co.uk/freeview.co.uk.channels.xml   (UK terrestrial)
    sites/player.ee.co.uk/player.ee.co.uk.channels.xml (EE TV, UK)
    sites/tvguide.com/tvguide.com.channels.xml         (US national)
    sites/meo.pt/meo.pt.channels.xml                   (Portugal; AXN/Star/AMC/
                                                        Hollywood feeds)
    sites/directv.com/directv.com.channels.xml         (US; BabyTV, MTV Live)
    sites/aljazeera.com/aljazeera.com.channels.xml     (Al Jazeera English)
  (Whether each returns data on a given day can only be confirmed by an actual
  online grab.) Channels in data/channels.js without a line here have no
  verified source and are left to the app's synthetic schedule.

  The workflow grabs into guide.xml then runs scripts/xmltv-to-guide.mjs to
  produce data/guide.json. See .github/workflows/epg.yml for the exact commands.
-->
